70. si: note si followed by si, the suppositions being parallel, and not contrasted with each other. Had they been contrasted stiae-sive or si -sin would have been needed. In one sentence in Livy (4, 5, 5) si is thus eight times repeated. — imbecilliore animo vel fortuna: these are the persons mentioned in 59 in quibusdam... fractior. —
